text: Wadala (Vidhan Sabha constituency) is one of the ten constituencies of the Maharashtra Legislative Assembly located in the Mumbai City district. It is a part of the Mumbai South Central (Lok Sabha constituency) along with five other assembly constituencies, viz Dharavi, Sion Koliwada, Mahim, from Mumbai City district and Chembur and Anushakti Nagar from Mumbai Suburban district. ==Members of Legislative Assembly== Key {| class="wikitable" |- !colspan="2"|Election!!Member!!Party |- | |1952-2008 |Seat did not exist | |- |style="background-color: " | | 2009 | rowspan="3" | Kalidas Kolambkar | rowspan="2" | Indian National Congress |- |style="background-color: " | | 2014 |- |style="background-color: " | | 2019 | Bharatiya Janata Party |} == Election results == ===2014 result=== ===2009 result=== ==See Also== List of constituencies of Maharashtra Legislative Assembly ==References== Category:Assembly constituencies of Mumbai Category:Mumbai City district Category:Assembly constituencies of Maharashtra
